Our courage fails us, our cheeks blanch3 our tears fall, though they are unavailing. But what is baser than to fret at the very threshold of peace? The reason, however, is, that we are stripped of all 'our goods, we have jettisoned our cargo os life and are in distress; for no part of it has been packed in the hold ; it has all been heaved overboard 81111 has drifted away. Men do not care how nobly they live, but only how long, although it is within the reach of every man to live nobly, but within no man's power to live long. Farewell.
